cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on pedestrian analysis using deep neural networks, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new attention-based deep neural network, which involves learning discriminative features from images, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on various datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
